1
00:00:47,160 --> 00:00:50,891
RA'S AL GHUL: I should never have
allied myself with a madman.

2
00:00:57,637 --> 00:00:58,763
where are they?

3
00:00:59,706 --> 00:01:01,264
in Sarajevo, sir.

4
00:01:02,476 --> 00:01:06,276
And he has the boy.

5
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:09,105
[GROANING]

6
00:01:10,684 --> 00:01:12,618
[GRUNTING]

7
00:01:15,389 --> 00:01:19,052
MAN:
wow, that looked like it really hurt:

8
00:01:23,230 --> 00:01:26,063
[ROBIN GRUNTING]

9
00:01:29,836 --> 00:01:31,565
whoa, now, hang on.

10
00:01:31,738 --> 00:01:34,138
That looked like it hurt a lot more:

11
00:01:34,574 --> 00:01:38,533
So let's try and clear this up, okay,
pumpkin?

12
00:01:38,712 --> 00:01:41,374
what hurts more? A?

13
00:01:42,616 --> 00:01:44,607
or B?

14
00:01:44,785 --> 00:01:46,047
Forehand?

15
00:01:46,953 --> 00:01:48,386
or backhand?

16
00:01:51,458 --> 00:01:53,722
[CACKLING]

17
00:01:59,966 --> 00:02:02,264
A little louder, lamb chop.

18
00:02:02,436 --> 00:02:06,429
I think you may have a collapsed lung.
That always impedes the oratory.

19
00:02:06,606 --> 00:02:08,233
[SPITS]

20
00:02:08,408 --> 00:02:09,841
[GRUNTS]

21
00:02:10,477 --> 00:02:12,172
Now, that was rude.

22
00:02:12,345 --> 00:02:14,905
The first boy blunder had some manners.

23
00:02:18,218 --> 00:02:20,652
I suppose I'm going to have
to teach you a lesson...

24
00:02:20,821 --> 00:02:23,790
...so you can better follow
in his footsteps.

25
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:28,356
No, I'm just gonna keep beating you
with this crowbar.

26
00:02:29,796 --> 00:02:32,390
[JOKER CACKLING]

27
00:02:39,005 --> 00:02:41,269
Where is the detective?

28
00:02:41,441 --> 00:02:43,102
MAN:
He's on his way.

29
00:02:48,849 --> 00:02:52,842
But, sir, he won't make it there in time.

30
00:03:01,561 --> 00:03:03,825
okay, kiddo, I gotta go.

31
00:03:03,997 --> 00:03:06,295
it's been fun though, right?

32
00:03:07,567 --> 00:03:10,536
well, maybe a smidge more fun for me
than you.

33
00:03:10,704 --> 00:03:13,400
I'm just guessing
since you're being awful quiet.

34
00:03:13,573 --> 00:03:19,068
Anyway, be a good boy.
Finish your homework and be in bed by 9.

35
00:03:19,246 --> 00:03:20,645
And, hey...

36
00:03:21,248 --> 00:03:26,686
...please tell the big man I said, "Hello."

37
00:03:26,853 --> 00:03:29,321
[CACKLING]

38
00:03:37,030 --> 00:03:38,793
[GROANING]

39
00:05:10,256 --> 00:05:12,190
No.

40
00:05:20,266 --> 00:05:22,234
Jason.

41
00:07:50,383 --> 00:07:51,441
MAN 1:
The hell you say.

42
00:07:51,918 --> 00:07:53,044
You didn't set this up?

43
00:07:53,219 --> 00:07:56,347
- Then whose party is this?
- I thought it was you east-side losers.

44
00:07:56,523 --> 00:08:00,482
You already rolled over for the Black Mask
and I figured you were gonna ask us in.

45
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:05,256
Rolled over? The Mask whacked
six of my crew in a month. Six.

46
00:08:05,431 --> 00:08:06,989
Some of my best people.

47
00:08:07,167 --> 00:08:08,657
So you set up this meet?

48
00:08:08,835 --> 00:08:10,826
No, I thought it was Chi Chi:

49
00:08:11,004 --> 00:08:12,130
wasn't my meet:

50
00:08:13,039 --> 00:08:16,600
oh, the hell with this. I'm gone.
You brain donors wanna hang around--

51
00:08:16,776 --> 00:08:18,141
MAN 2:
Sit down, Freddie.

52
00:08:20,180 --> 00:08:21,545
it's my meeting.

53
00:08:21,714 --> 00:08:23,375
CHI CHI: it's him.
- Batman?

54
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:24,642
we didn't do nothing.

55
00:08:24,818 --> 00:08:27,719
RED HOOD:
well, we all know that's a lie.

56
00:08:28,321 --> 00:08:30,118
- who the hell are you?
- Smoke him.

57
00:08:36,663 --> 00:08:38,028
RED HOOD:
I said, "Sit down."

58
00:08:38,198 --> 00:08:41,190
You wanna die?
There's easier ways to kill yourself.

59
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:44,666
RED HOOD: Yeah, like yelling at the guy
who's holding the AK-47.

60
00:08:44,838 --> 00:08:47,033
Listen to me,
you drug-peddling scumbags.

61
00:08:47,207 --> 00:08:49,698
I will be running the drug trade
from now on.

62
00:08:49,876 --> 00:08:52,936
You eight are the most prosperous
street dealers in Gotham.

63
00:08:53,112 --> 00:08:55,046
I'm offering you morons a deal.

64
00:08:55,215 --> 00:08:59,345
You go about your business as usual,
but kick up 40 percent to me.

65
00:08:59,519 --> 00:09:02,386
A much sweeter deal
than the scraps Black Mask is leaving you.

66
00:09:02,555 --> 00:09:07,390
in return, you will have total protection
from both Black Mask and Batman.

67
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:09,721
But you stay away from kids
and school yards.

68
00:09:10,330 --> 00:09:12,457
No dealing to children, got it?

69
00:09:12,632 --> 00:09:15,396
if you do, you're dead.

70
00:09:15,568 --> 00:09:18,799
okay, crazy man,
this is all very generous.

71
00:09:18,972 --> 00:09:20,735
But why in the hell
should we listen to you?

72
00:09:30,550 --> 00:09:31,778
[CHI CHI VOMITS]

73
00:09:31,951 --> 00:09:33,145
Damn.

74
00:09:33,319 --> 00:09:35,947
RED HOOD: Those are the heads
of all of your lieutenants.

75
00:09:36,122 --> 00:09:37,714
That took me two hours.

76
00:09:37,891 --> 00:09:40,689
You wanna see what I can get done
in a whole evening?

77
00:09:40,860 --> 00:09:42,293
Make no mistake.

78
00:09:42,462 --> 00:09:45,090
I'm not asking you to kick in with me.

79
00:09:45,265 --> 00:09:47,130
I'm telling you.

80
00:09:55,708 --> 00:09:57,733
Forty percent works for me.

81
00:10:05,911 --> 00:10:07,742
[TIRES SCREECHING]

82
00:10:10,516 --> 00:10:12,609
- Go, go, go!
- where's Raymond and Denny?

83
00:10:12,785 --> 00:10:14,946
- He got them. Just grabbed them up.
MAN: Screw it.

84
00:10:15,121 --> 00:10:16,782
Just go, get us out of here.

85
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,622
I think I lost him.

86
00:10:22,795 --> 00:10:25,059
- You think I lost him?
- I think you lost him.

87
00:10:25,231 --> 00:10:27,222
I think we're good.

88
00:10:27,767 --> 00:10:30,634
No, you're anything but good.

89
00:10:57,396 --> 00:10:59,057
[GROANING]

90
00:10:59,231 --> 00:11:00,425
[YELLS]

91
00:11:03,269 --> 00:11:04,497
who are you working for?

92
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:05,796
Nobody.

93
00:11:05,971 --> 00:11:08,166
Look, we just boosted the truck and--

94
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:11,571
Lie to me again
and crashing into a wall head-on...

95
00:11:11,744 --> 00:11:14,338
...will be the least painful activity
of your evening:

96
00:11:14,513 --> 00:11:16,003
No, I swear to--

97
00:11:16,182 --> 00:11:18,742
[BEEPING]

98
00:11:32,098 --> 00:11:34,566
- what is that?
- Your cargo.

99
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:42,398
it's called Amazo.

100
00:11:42,575 --> 00:11:44,236
what the hell is an Amazo?

101
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:46,469
A highly advanced, cybernetic android...

102
00:11:46,645 --> 00:11:49,671
...equipped with the ability
to absorb the power of super humans.

103
00:11:49,849 --> 00:11:51,316
what kind of super humans?

104
00:11:58,023 --> 00:11:59,547
Big ones.

105
00:12:12,738 --> 00:12:16,105
NIGHTWING: Packs quite the punch
for a toaster on steroids, huh?

106
00:12:16,842 --> 00:12:19,436
- Need a hand?
- No.

107
00:12:20,679 --> 00:12:23,876
NIGHTWING: okay, well,
how about I just stick around and watch?

108
00:12:36,128 --> 00:12:38,824
who's that other one?
The pretty boy in the leotard?

109
00:12:38,998 --> 00:12:41,762
That's Nightwing.
He was the Bat's first sidekick.

110
00:12:41,934 --> 00:12:44,164
The first Robin.

111
00:13:00,352 --> 00:13:03,344
- I think you'll have to do better than that.
- I did.

112
00:13:05,991 --> 00:13:07,015
[BEEPING]

113
00:13:11,197 --> 00:13:14,132
NIGHTWING: will that do any good?
BATMAN: it'll slow it down.

114
00:13:15,134 --> 00:13:16,965
You think so?

115
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:23,240
Get to higher ground.

116
00:13:27,346 --> 00:13:29,075
NIGHTWING: Did you know he could fly?
- Move!

117
00:13:35,721 --> 00:13:38,212
I wouldn't be offended
by a few suggestions.

118
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:40,654
He has the same weak points
as a human being.

119
00:13:40,826 --> 00:13:42,885
Got it. This might sting a bit.

120
00:13:43,062 --> 00:13:45,155
[YELLING]

121
00:14:05,184 --> 00:14:07,744
Lasers. He's got lasers.

122
00:14:15,861 --> 00:14:18,853
I don't think putty in his eyes
is gonna hurt him.

123
00:14:23,535 --> 00:14:26,368
But plastique will. Nice.

124
00:14:41,954 --> 00:14:44,320
BATMAN: This shipment was meant
for the Black Mask.

125
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:46,048
I doubt you're behind this.

126
00:14:46,225 --> 00:14:50,161
- who do you work for?
- I swear. we're not working for anybody.

127
00:14:50,329 --> 00:14:52,297
This was our gig, all our idea.

128
00:14:53,299 --> 00:14:55,460
- Let it go.
- Right.

129
00:14:57,803 --> 00:14:59,100
[SCREAMS]

130
00:15:00,239 --> 00:15:03,299
I'll talk, I'll talk. Just stop. Just stop!

131
00:15:05,311 --> 00:15:08,144
The Red Hood.
we're working for the Red Hood.

132
00:15:08,314 --> 00:15:10,214
we don't have any choice. He's got--

133
00:15:10,382 --> 00:15:12,043
[BULLETS WHIZZING]

134
00:15:17,756 --> 00:15:19,986
The shots came from the rooftop.
A sniper.

135
00:15:21,827 --> 00:15:23,192
BATMAN:
A good one.

136
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:31,164
NIGHTWING: See him?
- Yeah.

137
00:15:35,074 --> 00:15:36,666
NIGHTWING:
Hey, wait.

138
00:15:37,843 --> 00:15:39,504
Right. Leave me with them.

139
00:16:17,516 --> 00:16:19,347
[CAR HORN HONKING]

140
00:17:36,595 --> 00:17:38,790
God, please, no. Stay away.

141
00:17:38,964 --> 00:17:40,795
it's a setup. wait.

142
00:17:42,301 --> 00:17:43,996
I'm not a crook, I swear.

143
00:17:47,506 --> 00:17:50,407
No!

144
00:18:03,856 --> 00:18:06,120
RED HOOD:
Hard to forget that night, huh?

145
00:18:06,758 --> 00:18:10,250
in a way, Batman,
this was the site of your first great failure.

146
00:18:10,429 --> 00:18:14,490
Maybe your greatest,
but certainly not your last, right?

147
00:18:16,135 --> 00:18:18,296
Ah, memories.

148
00:18:58,477 --> 00:19:00,570
DICK: This bit of Intel
is what brought me to town.

149
00:19:00,746 --> 00:19:04,512
Good thing I've always had perfect timing.
Take a look.

150
00:19:08,687 --> 00:19:12,680
I got this shot from a snitch. He says that
this guy's been making some serious moves.

151
00:19:12,858 --> 00:19:13,984
The Red Hood.

152
00:19:14,159 --> 00:19:16,593
Might be.
He bears a resemblance to the original.

153
00:19:18,363 --> 00:19:20,797
BRUCE:
Several criminals have utilized this persona.

154
00:19:20,966 --> 00:19:23,628
DICK:
one criminal of particular interest, though.

155
00:19:23,802 --> 00:19:26,566
- But he's locked up.
- Not his m.o. either.

156
00:19:26,738 --> 00:19:30,936
There's been an up tick in heavy trafficking,
but crime is down.

157
00:19:31,109 --> 00:19:32,167
ALFRED:
indeed it is.

158
00:19:32,344 --> 00:19:35,507
Master Bruce got almost three hours sleep
in the last two days.

159
00:19:35,681 --> 00:19:37,478
True busman's holiday.

160
00:19:37,649 --> 00:19:39,480
But he is locked up.

161
00:19:39,651 --> 00:19:42,085
Like, a lot locked up.

162
00:19:42,254 --> 00:19:44,552
Maybe we should go for a visit.

163
00:19:47,159 --> 00:19:51,095
Could you just once say,
"Let's get in the car"? is that so hard?

164
00:20:20,759 --> 00:20:24,422
[LAUGHTER ECHOING]

165
00:20:31,703 --> 00:20:34,797
You look good. Been working out?

166
00:20:35,274 --> 00:20:37,640
You could probably use a little sun.

167
00:20:38,477 --> 00:20:41,605
Then again, who am I to talk?

168
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:43,941
[CACKLING]

169
00:20:49,921 --> 00:20:52,412
BATMAN:
He's calling himself the Red Hood:

170
00:20:53,191 --> 00:20:54,590
what do you know about it?

171
00:20:55,294 --> 00:20:57,785
That he has horrible taste.

172
00:20:57,963 --> 00:20:59,931
when I wore that number, it was classy.

173
00:21:00,098 --> 00:21:03,124
More flashy maitre d'
than motorcycle fetish.

174
00:21:03,302 --> 00:21:05,099
oh, these kids today.

175
00:21:05,270 --> 00:21:08,603
if you're behind this in any way,
we will find out.

176
00:21:08,774 --> 00:21:12,574
- You're not--
- oh, Bird Boy, you're so much less fun now.

177
00:21:12,744 --> 00:21:16,874
All grown up and in your big-boy pants.

178
00:21:17,049 --> 00:21:20,951
Still, better off than his replacement,
right?

179
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:26,048
Even tougher making with the yuks
when you're worm food, huh?

180
00:21:37,569 --> 00:21:39,628
You gonna do it this time?

181
00:21:39,805 --> 00:21:43,571
or you just gonna put me
in another body cast for six months?

182
00:21:54,152 --> 00:21:56,643
So disappointing.

183
00:21:56,888 --> 00:21:59,516
But back to the matter at hand...

184
00:21:59,691 --> 00:22:01,784
...this new hoody.

185
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:05,293
You really think I would stir up
so much trouble...

186
00:22:05,464 --> 00:22:08,922
...and not make sure
you knew it was me?

187
00:22:09,101 --> 00:22:11,365
[CACKLING]

188
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:30,882
I know you've never met him before,
but be cool.

189
00:22:31,056 --> 00:22:32,580
This here is the Black Mask.

190
00:22:32,758 --> 00:22:36,717
The first boss to gain control
of the entire city in 20 years.

191
00:22:36,895 --> 00:22:39,295
whatever he wants in Gotham, he gets.

192
00:22:40,432 --> 00:22:45,335
But his appearance
takes a bit to warm up to.

193
00:22:45,504 --> 00:22:48,064
MAN:
He did what? what?

194
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:51,232
oh, good, he's pissed.

195
00:22:52,477 --> 00:22:55,310
WOMAN: our concern is the one
who ordered the theft of the android.

196
00:22:55,480 --> 00:22:57,641
He goes by the name of Red Hood.

197
00:22:58,216 --> 00:23:00,047
MAN:
I don't care what he's calling himself.

198
00:23:00,218 --> 00:23:02,743
Do you idiots know
how many bidders I had on Amazo?

199
00:23:02,921 --> 00:23:06,823
A list of puppet dictators
and psychos as long as my arm.

200
00:23:06,992 --> 00:23:09,153
Millions shot right to hell.

201
00:23:09,327 --> 00:23:12,262
- And whose money is that?
- Your money.

202
00:23:12,864 --> 00:23:15,992
My money. Mine.

203
00:23:16,401 --> 00:23:18,335
This score was a game changer.

204
00:23:18,503 --> 00:23:22,599
Amazo was going buy my way up
into high-end international trafficking.

205
00:23:23,275 --> 00:23:27,871
Now I'm forced to keep rooting around
in this local leg-breaking garbage.

206
00:23:28,046 --> 00:23:32,676
And he gives me bat trouble,
who blows the damn robot's head off!

207
00:23:32,851 --> 00:23:37,151
I could have at least sold it for scrap,
but Batman kept it.

208
00:23:37,322 --> 00:23:40,257
Yes, Batman likes to keep things.

209
00:23:41,092 --> 00:23:46,223
- Look, this circus act, this Red Foot--
- Red Hood.

210
00:23:46,398 --> 00:23:48,093
whatever.

211
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:51,995
He's dead. Take care of him.

212
00:23:54,272 --> 00:23:56,206
You, new guy.

213
00:23:56,842 --> 00:23:59,208
- Sir:
BLACK MASK: Don't be nervous, kid.

214
00:23:59,711 --> 00:24:04,478
But if you keep staring at me like that,
I'm gonna cut your eyes out.

215
00:24:09,588 --> 00:24:11,317
[GROANING]

216
00:24:11,490 --> 00:24:15,688
- Give me the specs on tonight's shipment.
LEON: Yes, sir.

217
00:24:15,861 --> 00:24:18,728
it's 10 cases of assorted SMGs
and PDWs...

218
00:24:18,897 --> 00:24:22,594
...along with 5000 .45 caliber ACP rounds,
your personal favorite...

219
00:24:22,767 --> 00:24:24,166
...and two cases of RPGs.

220
00:24:24,970 --> 00:24:28,337
it's all bought and paid for,
so this is strictly a delivery, not a buy.

221
00:24:28,507 --> 00:24:31,670
in view of recent events, I've taken
the liberty of doubling security...

222
00:24:31,843 --> 00:24:33,435
...and switching the drop spot.

223
00:24:33,612 --> 00:24:35,170
RED HOOD:
That sounds like a plan.

224
00:24:51,897 --> 00:24:55,731
CO-PILOT: what are they waiting around for?
- Seriously.

225
00:24:57,202 --> 00:25:00,899
Hey, protocol says I'm only supposed to be
on the ground for six minutes.

226
00:25:02,407 --> 00:25:04,398
RED HOOD:
it's okay. I won't be staying that long.

227
00:25:25,096 --> 00:25:26,927
And I almost thought he wouldn't show.

228
00:25:28,833 --> 00:25:31,859
You know what I missed most
about running with you? The toys.

229
00:25:32,037 --> 00:25:33,629
Stay sharp. we're not done.

230
00:25:33,805 --> 00:25:35,898
RED HOOD:
You wanna dance? Let's dance.

231
00:25:37,909 --> 00:25:39,501
- is that gonna hold?
- No.

232
00:25:39,678 --> 00:25:41,703
So you want me to--? should i--?

233
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:44,474
okay, I'll just take care of this.

234
00:26:18,984 --> 00:26:21,350
RED HOOD:
okay then. Nice night for a run.

235
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:45,228
- He's good.
- Yes, he's putting on quite a show.

236
00:28:02,587 --> 00:28:04,179
He's very good.

237
00:28:07,625 --> 00:28:09,252
we got him.

238
00:28:17,235 --> 00:28:19,965
- That's impressive.
- Nothing we haven't seen before.

239
00:28:20,138 --> 00:28:21,435
if you say so.

240
00:28:26,778 --> 00:28:28,643
Think we lost him?

241
00:28:28,813 --> 00:28:30,872
[BEEPING]

242
00:28:31,049 --> 00:28:32,380
Move!

243
00:28:32,550 --> 00:28:33,847
[BEEPING RAPIDLY]

244
00:28:45,497 --> 00:28:47,397
[GROANS]

245
00:28:48,633 --> 00:28:50,863
RED HOOD:
You haven't lost your touch--

246
00:29:08,486 --> 00:29:11,944
He's got some moves, huh?
And as much I hate to belabor a point...

247
00:29:12,123 --> 00:29:14,557
And still that is often
exactly what you do.

248
00:29:14,726 --> 00:29:16,626
I'm chatty. it's part of my charm.

249
00:29:16,795 --> 00:29:19,025
I'm saying that our boy here
has some skills.

250
00:29:19,564 --> 00:29:22,965
He's been trained and trained well.
Like right there. That.

251
00:29:23,134 --> 00:29:26,592
He sliced that cable
off his ankle before it went taut.

252
00:29:26,771 --> 00:29:29,706
You don't just do that.
That has to be practiced. Learned.

253
00:29:29,874 --> 00:29:32,035
- And then there's the knife.
- what about it?

254
00:29:32,544 --> 00:29:34,535
You know many knives
that can cut my lines?

255
00:29:35,079 --> 00:29:38,845
- Not many.
- No. Not many.

256
00:29:39,017 --> 00:29:42,953
well, look, we obviously have got
ourselves a player, we-- ow!

257
00:29:43,121 --> 00:29:44,986
BRUCE:
Alfred, take him home.

258
00:29:45,156 --> 00:29:46,646
Bruce, I can still help.

259
00:29:47,659 --> 00:29:49,183
You already have.

260
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:50,827
Thank you.

261
00:29:50,995 --> 00:29:52,826
Go rest up.

262
00:29:53,431 --> 00:29:54,557
okay.

263
00:29:54,732 --> 00:29:57,565
But you know where to find me
if you need me.

264
00:29:58,803 --> 00:30:00,862
He did just thank me, right?

265
00:30:01,039 --> 00:30:03,564
- indeed he did, sir.
DICK: weird.

266
00:30:10,148 --> 00:30:11,911
RED HOOD:
You haven't lost your touch--

267
00:30:12,083 --> 00:30:14,210
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS
ON VIDEO]

268
00:30:18,623 --> 00:30:20,181
You haven't lost your touch--

269
00:30:21,693 --> 00:30:23,024
--your touch, Bru--

270
00:30:28,900 --> 00:30:31,027
You haven't lost your touch, Bruce.

271
00:30:55,860 --> 00:30:57,555
[ROBIN LAUGHS]

272
00:31:10,875 --> 00:31:13,275
ROBIN:
whoo-hoo!

273
00:31:13,444 --> 00:31:15,275
You guys having a party?

274
00:31:17,749 --> 00:31:21,480
- I guess our invite got lost.
- it's over, Riddler.

275
00:31:34,265 --> 00:31:38,429
Riddle me this. what's green and purple
but covered in red and yellow?

276
00:31:44,509 --> 00:31:48,070
You. when I land on your sorry butt.

277
00:31:48,246 --> 00:31:49,645
MAN:
Don't move or I'll--

278
00:31:49,814 --> 00:31:51,975
You'll what? Shoot me?

279
00:32:06,798 --> 00:32:09,699
Twenty rounds a second
and you were still too slow.

280
00:32:11,035 --> 00:32:12,593
I'm not slow, punk.

281
00:32:13,571 --> 00:32:15,129
- Me neither.
- I've got him.

282
00:32:16,941 --> 00:32:18,966
[GRUNTING]

283
00:32:19,944 --> 00:32:21,775
Robin!

284
00:32:24,282 --> 00:32:26,045
I had to take him down.

285
00:32:26,217 --> 00:32:27,878
You shattered his collar bone.

286
00:32:28,052 --> 00:32:29,246
He's a drug-dealing pimp.

287
00:32:29,420 --> 00:32:32,548
I didn't think I had to prop up some pillows
before I took him out.

288
00:32:32,724 --> 00:32:35,056
we needed him. He would've talked.

289
00:32:35,226 --> 00:32:36,818
But you put him into shock.

290
00:32:38,329 --> 00:32:39,660
Sorry.

291
00:32:39,831 --> 00:32:41,196
That was dumb.

292
00:32:41,366 --> 00:32:43,300
But he deserved it.

293
00:33:00,051 --> 00:33:03,418
BLACK MASK: Maybe my last request
was too mired in subtlety.

294
00:33:04,455 --> 00:33:06,082
I want this man dead.

295
00:33:07,158 --> 00:33:10,855
when I say "dead," I mean seriously dead.

296
00:33:11,396 --> 00:33:13,694
Beaten, broken.

297
00:33:13,865 --> 00:33:18,029
His-head-mounted-on-my-wall
kind of dead!

298
00:33:18,202 --> 00:33:19,533
Understood.

299
00:33:19,704 --> 00:33:22,366
we'll be taking further precautions
at every transaction--

300
00:33:22,540 --> 00:33:26,670
Screw that.
Time he learns that this is a contact sport.

301
00:33:26,844 --> 00:33:28,607
we're going on offense.

302
00:33:28,780 --> 00:33:32,682
Rough up his business.
Something big. Something loud.

303
00:33:32,850 --> 00:33:36,946
when he shows up to shut us down,
have a party waiting for him.

304
00:33:37,121 --> 00:33:38,611
And when I say "party"...

305
00:33:38,790 --> 00:33:43,693
...I actually mean a whole lot of people
who are gonna kill him!

306
00:33:43,861 --> 00:33:47,319
- I figured.
- Just being clear.

307
00:33:49,834 --> 00:33:51,768
[SIGHS]

308
00:33:57,942 --> 00:33:59,068
[TIRES SCREECHING]

309
00:34:00,912 --> 00:34:02,140
[ENGINE REVS]

310
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:04,948
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

311
00:34:16,394 --> 00:34:18,658
what are you doing? we're protected.

312
00:34:18,830 --> 00:34:20,491
we pay up to the Red Hood.

313
00:34:20,665 --> 00:34:22,326
is that right?

314
00:34:26,404 --> 00:34:27,735
Cute.

315
00:34:48,626 --> 00:34:51,527
Do you know who you're messing with?

316
00:34:51,696 --> 00:34:53,721
Yeah, Tyler Bramford.

317
00:34:53,898 --> 00:34:57,800
You're a club owner and some big damned
drug dealer in the East Quarter, right?

318
00:34:57,969 --> 00:35:03,202
I am the East Quarter drug trade,
you stupid bags of--

319
00:35:03,374 --> 00:35:04,773
Manners, fatty.

320
00:35:04,942 --> 00:35:07,877
I don't care who takes care of you.
You watch your mouth.

321
00:35:08,045 --> 00:35:10,775
Then you know who's got my back.

322
00:35:10,948 --> 00:35:12,381
You know who I answer to.

323
00:35:12,550 --> 00:35:14,450
Sure: The Red Hood.

324
00:35:14,619 --> 00:35:18,487
And we work for the man
who's gonna take back what's his.

325
00:35:19,090 --> 00:35:23,322
CHICO: So at the expense
of your very wide butt...

326
00:35:24,996 --> 00:35:27,157
...we're sending your boss a message.

327
00:35:31,035 --> 00:35:32,866
[SCREAMING]

328
00:35:34,205 --> 00:35:35,866
RED HOOD:
okay.

329
00:35:36,874 --> 00:35:38,808
what's the message?

330
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:43,913
WOMAN:
A simple one, actually.

331
00:35:46,050 --> 00:35:48,416
want to guess what it might be?

332
00:35:49,220 --> 00:35:50,710
RED HOOD:
I have a few ideas.

333
00:36:19,884 --> 00:36:22,284
Any of you hired guns even know
who I am?

334
00:36:22,453 --> 00:36:24,614
BATON:
You are our target.

335
00:36:35,733 --> 00:36:36,995
RED HOOD:
ow.

336
00:36:37,168 --> 00:36:41,798
So you four have all this power
and all you do with it is kill for money?

337
00:36:41,973 --> 00:36:44,737
BULK: From what I hear,
we've got that in common.

338
00:36:45,776 --> 00:36:46,902
RED HOOD:
You heard wrong.

339
00:36:59,724 --> 00:37:02,215
BATON:
I thought you'd put up more of a fight.

340
00:37:02,793 --> 00:37:04,954
RED HOOD:
oh, the fight hasn't started yet.

341
00:37:05,129 --> 00:37:06,460
I'm just stalling.

342
00:37:20,745 --> 00:37:23,976
- what the hell took you so long?
- Shut up and fight.

343
00:37:24,949 --> 00:37:26,883
[GRUNTING]

344
00:37:53,010 --> 00:37:54,978
[SCREAMING]

345
00:38:01,419 --> 00:38:02,716
[POWERING UP]

346
00:38:02,887 --> 00:38:04,184
[SCREAMING]

347
00:38:25,976 --> 00:38:27,466
RED HOOD:
I gotta say.

348
00:38:27,645 --> 00:38:28,907
I missed watching you work.

349
00:38:30,848 --> 00:38:32,213
Look out!

350
00:38:56,173 --> 00:38:58,004
RED HOOD:
Awful close.

351
00:38:58,175 --> 00:38:59,540
You afraid you'll miss?

352
00:38:59,710 --> 00:39:01,871
SHOT:
Black Mask just wants a body.

353
00:39:02,046 --> 00:39:04,947
- we don't need your head.
BATMAN: Let him go.

354
00:39:05,116 --> 00:39:07,107
And step away.

355
00:39:07,284 --> 00:39:09,184
SHOT:
A Taser?

356
00:39:10,254 --> 00:39:12,347
Nail me and you'll electrocute both of us.

357
00:39:13,524 --> 00:39:15,287
RED HOOD:
Maybe that's what he has in mind.

358
00:39:20,631 --> 00:39:22,064
No!

359
00:39:24,735 --> 00:39:26,862
RED HOOD:
Just be happy I only killed one of them.

360
00:39:27,037 --> 00:39:28,527
They're all assassins.

361
00:39:28,706 --> 00:39:29,866
And what are you?

362
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:31,701
RED HOOD:
I'm cleaning up Gotham.

363
00:39:31,876 --> 00:39:33,275
More than you ever did.

364
00:39:33,444 --> 00:39:38,006
You're stealing territory from Black Mask
and killing anyone who gets in your way.

365
00:39:38,182 --> 00:39:40,742
RED HOOD:
Black Mask is just a part of the plan.

366
00:39:40,918 --> 00:39:43,614
Plan? You're becoming a crime lord.

367
00:39:43,788 --> 00:39:47,622
Yes. You can't stop crime.
That's what you never understood.

368
00:39:47,792 --> 00:39:49,225
I'm controlling it.

369
00:39:50,394 --> 00:39:54,125
You wanna rule them by fear. But what do
you do with the ones who aren't afraid?

370
00:39:54,298 --> 00:39:56,960
I'm doing what you won't,
I'm taking them out.

371
00:39:58,469 --> 00:40:01,063
Tell me what happened to you.
Let me help.

372
00:40:03,140 --> 00:40:04,801
RED HOOD:
it's too late.

373
00:40:05,443 --> 00:40:06,569
You had your chance.

374
00:40:13,150 --> 00:40:16,017
And I'm just getting started.

375
00:41:13,577 --> 00:41:19,516
BLACK MASK: Son of a-- Are you telling me
that scumbag stole my guns again?

376
00:41:20,050 --> 00:41:24,487
No, sir: He destroyed them.
Blew up the truck, the drivers....

377
00:41:24,655 --> 00:41:28,147
Damn it. of all the-- Damn it!

378
00:41:28,325 --> 00:41:32,261
Previously, he was just enlisting anyone
under our province to come work for him.

379
00:41:32,429 --> 00:41:36,024
Now he just seems to be killing them.

380
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:38,668
oh, so now we've got another Batman?

381
00:41:38,836 --> 00:41:40,531
one who doesn't mind the blood?

382
00:41:40,704 --> 00:41:42,604
No, sir, he's no Batman.

383
00:41:42,773 --> 00:41:45,298
He's still taking huge cuts
from off the streets.

384
00:41:45,476 --> 00:41:48,172
But now
he's eliminating the competition.

385
00:41:48,345 --> 00:41:49,710
He's coming after you.

386
00:41:51,515 --> 00:41:52,743
[CLEARS THROAT]

387
00:41:55,252 --> 00:41:56,549
[YELLS]

388
00:41:56,720 --> 00:42:00,019
You wanna tell me
why this guy ain't dead?

389
00:42:00,190 --> 00:42:03,353
we're trying.
we sent the Fearsome Hand of Four.

390
00:42:04,895 --> 00:42:08,695
Four? Guess they're gonna need
a new name.

391
00:42:08,866 --> 00:42:12,563
why hasn't Batman wiped this little smear
off the face of the planet?

392
00:42:12,736 --> 00:42:14,670
Maybe he doesn't want to.

393
00:42:14,838 --> 00:42:17,807
Perhaps he's letting you
and the Red Hood war it out.

394
00:42:17,975 --> 00:42:21,103
- He could be waiting--
- To take on the winner?

395
00:42:21,545 --> 00:42:25,140
what do you think this is?
A tennis tournament?

396
00:42:25,316 --> 00:42:27,580
- I'm just saying...
BLACK MASK: You're an idiot.

397
00:42:27,751 --> 00:42:29,309
And you don't know Batman.

398
00:42:29,486 --> 00:42:32,887
He's not letting this lunatic just run wild.

399
00:42:33,057 --> 00:42:35,423
He can't catch him either.

400
00:42:35,626 --> 00:42:38,925
or it's something else.

401
00:42:39,430 --> 00:42:41,125
Can't you feel it?

402
00:42:41,298 --> 00:42:43,766
we're stuck in the damn crossfire.

403
00:42:52,843 --> 00:42:54,743
oh, hell.

404
00:42:59,149 --> 00:43:00,673
Sir?

405
00:43:01,385 --> 00:43:04,980
RED HOOD: wow, he sure can move
when he really wants to.

406
00:43:20,804 --> 00:43:24,069
- You okay, sir?
- I'm not dead.

407
00:43:24,241 --> 00:43:26,072
So that's something.

408
00:43:26,243 --> 00:43:27,403
okay.

409
00:43:27,578 --> 00:43:30,945
- Time to change up the ground war.
- How so, sir?

410
00:43:31,115 --> 00:43:34,448
I'm being forced into negotiating
with a psychotic.

411
00:43:34,618 --> 00:43:36,176
That doesn't sound good.

412
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:38,085
No.

413
00:43:38,255 --> 00:43:40,849
it's going to be a nightmare.

414
00:43:53,671 --> 00:43:56,003
Hey, fellas,
10 minutes to bed check, right?

415
00:43:56,173 --> 00:43:59,165
- Terry? what the hell are you doing here?
- You miss me?

416
00:43:59,343 --> 00:44:03,006
I'm covering Rothman's shift.
He's got the flu, bronchitis or something.

417
00:44:03,180 --> 00:44:06,672
we got this. why don't you grab us some Joe?
we'll meet you in the south wing.

418
00:44:06,850 --> 00:44:08,010
That's not protocol.

419
00:44:08,185 --> 00:44:11,154
Come on, I'm bored,
I need to stretch my legs: Let's get--

420
00:44:11,321 --> 00:44:12,447
[BULLET WHIZZES]

421
00:44:14,358 --> 00:44:16,019
Sorry, schedule to keep.

422
00:44:17,294 --> 00:44:18,886
MAC:
You didn't have to kill him.

423
00:44:19,063 --> 00:44:22,055
one, yes, I did.
Two, we're paying you a ton.

424
00:44:22,232 --> 00:44:25,224
So, three, shut your gob
and open the damn door.

425
00:44:40,350 --> 00:44:43,717
- Does he know what's going on?
- He knows he's leaving.

426
00:44:44,922 --> 00:44:47,789
JOKER:
it's gonna be a sleepover, right?

427
00:44:48,659 --> 00:44:51,287
I packed my toothbrush.

428
00:45:10,481 --> 00:45:14,247
- Do you need more light, sir?
- No: I can see fine.

429
00:45:34,872 --> 00:45:37,033
well, there you have it.

430
00:45:37,207 --> 00:45:38,731
He's still at rest.

431
00:45:38,909 --> 00:45:40,843
No, he isn't.

432
00:45:42,846 --> 00:45:44,973
That's not flesh.

433
00:45:53,423 --> 00:45:57,189
- Master Bruce, you can't blame yourself--
BRUCE: it was stupid and careless.

434
00:45:57,361 --> 00:45:58,953
Body was made of high-end latex.

435
00:45:59,129 --> 00:46:01,962
if I'd bothered to look inside
when I brought him home....

436
00:46:02,132 --> 00:46:05,431
Sir, please, remember how distraught
you were. Even I found it hard--

437
00:46:06,637 --> 00:46:08,127
Stupid and careless.

438
00:46:09,606 --> 00:46:13,372
- where are you going?
- To talk to the man who did this.

439
00:46:26,456 --> 00:46:29,550
I hope you understand the trouble
I've gone through...

440
00:46:29,726 --> 00:46:32,559
...to arrange this little get-together here.

441
00:46:32,729 --> 00:46:36,893
A lot of money. A lot of dead meat.

442
00:46:43,373 --> 00:46:45,841
Look, I've got a problem.

443
00:46:46,009 --> 00:46:49,570
And you are absolutely the man
who possesses the gifts...

444
00:46:49,746 --> 00:46:52,544
...to take care of this problem.

445
00:46:52,716 --> 00:46:55,514
I need you to murder the Red Hood.

446
00:46:55,686 --> 00:46:57,153
You think you can handle that?

447
00:46:59,523 --> 00:47:01,047
[COUGHS]

448
00:47:01,225 --> 00:47:03,523
May I have some water?

449
00:47:19,610 --> 00:47:22,272
[JOKER CACKLING]

450
00:47:28,318 --> 00:47:32,448
I'm going to need something to wear...

451
00:47:32,623 --> 00:47:34,682
...and a very big truck.

452
00:47:35,325 --> 00:47:37,691
Sure: Anything else?

453
00:47:38,195 --> 00:47:40,629
I'll need some guys.

454
00:47:41,531 --> 00:47:45,023
Not these guys
because, well, they're kind of dead.

455
00:48:26,443 --> 00:48:28,775
what did you do to Jason?

456
00:48:28,946 --> 00:48:32,609
Act like you don't know what I'm talking
about and I'll dislocate the shoulder.

457
00:48:32,783 --> 00:48:33,943
That's just to start.

458
00:48:34,117 --> 00:48:38,417
if you haven't disabled the roof sensors,
my guards will be here in under a minute.

459
00:48:38,622 --> 00:48:39,680
Answer me.

460
00:48:41,625 --> 00:48:42,649
I'm willing to...

461
00:48:42,826 --> 00:48:46,489
...but it'll be more expedient if you hand me
the communicator in my pocket...

462
00:48:46,663 --> 00:48:49,632
...and I call off my men.

463
00:48:53,704 --> 00:48:56,002
Commander, this is Ra's Al Ghul.

464
00:48:56,173 --> 00:48:58,038
Stand down.

465
00:48:58,208 --> 00:49:02,201
I will be entertaining a guest
in my study.

466
00:49:05,949 --> 00:49:08,281
You remember
when we last became embattled?

467
00:49:08,452 --> 00:49:10,511
You were planning to blow up banks.

468
00:49:10,687 --> 00:49:13,247
Accurate, if inelegant.

469
00:49:13,423 --> 00:49:17,223
I was in the midst of toppling the economy
of Europe...

470
00:49:17,394 --> 00:49:20,295
...but you were on to me.

471
00:49:20,831 --> 00:49:22,526
I sought a distraction.

472
00:49:23,100 --> 00:49:25,466
So I hired the Joker.

473
00:49:30,774 --> 00:49:32,742
When your paths crossed in Bosnia...

474
00:49:33,677 --> 00:49:36,237
...it was to appear
that you had stumbled upon him.

475
00:49:48,392 --> 00:49:52,192
He was paid extremely well for what
was intended to be a wild-goose chase.

476
00:49:58,035 --> 00:50:02,233
Then he murdered the boy.

477
00:50:02,973 --> 00:50:05,339
That was not by design.

478
00:50:05,509 --> 00:50:09,343
I'm afraid I overestimated my ability
to control the Joker...

479
00:50:09,513 --> 00:50:12,971
...just as I underestimated his madness.

480
00:50:13,150 --> 00:50:14,515
it grieved me, sir...

481
00:50:14,684 --> 00:50:17,084
...to be a party to something so brutal.

482
00:50:17,254 --> 00:50:19,586
You've never shied away
from drawing blood.

483
00:50:19,756 --> 00:50:22,418
True, but always with purpose.

484
00:50:22,592 --> 00:50:24,492
Always with greater goals.

485
00:50:24,661 --> 00:50:27,289
This was simply an unnecessary casualty.

486
00:50:27,464 --> 00:50:31,798
As penance,
I chose not to make war with you again...

487
00:50:31,968 --> 00:50:34,732
...and to attempt
to rectify this disservice.

488
00:50:34,905 --> 00:50:36,065
Rectify?

489
00:50:36,540 --> 00:50:37,734
Yes:

490
00:50:37,908 --> 00:50:41,366
I had hoped to return to you
what you had lost.

491
00:50:43,547 --> 00:50:47,039
l have walked this world
for nearly six centuries.

492
00:50:47,217 --> 00:50:48,411
As you know...

493
00:50:48,585 --> 00:50:53,522
...I achieve this by bathing in
the rejuvenating waters of the Lazarus Pit.

494
00:51:07,370 --> 00:51:09,065
Along with its healing abilities...

495
00:51:09,239 --> 00:51:13,232
...it has long been rumored
that it is capable of an even greater feat...

496
00:51:13,810 --> 00:51:16,074
...to raise the dead.

497
00:51:18,882 --> 00:51:22,249
Procuring the remains of your partner
was not difficult.

498
00:51:22,419 --> 00:51:26,219
You had come to Bosnia
under the guise of Bruce Wayne...

499
00:51:26,823 --> 00:51:29,690
...and you chose to depart as such.

500
00:51:30,827 --> 00:51:32,624
You even concocted the cover story...

501
00:51:32,796 --> 00:51:36,698
...that young Jason had died in a bombing
in Sarajevo.

502
00:51:37,334 --> 00:51:39,461
This made it easy for me.

503
00:51:40,770 --> 00:51:44,171
All it took was a few payoffs
to replace his body.

504
00:51:48,345 --> 00:51:51,143
I felt confident
that you would not perform an autopsy...

505
00:51:51,882 --> 00:51:54,783
...even if you had,
we still would have bought enough time.

506
00:51:54,951 --> 00:51:56,316
But my plan...

507
00:51:57,787 --> 00:52:03,384
...well, detective,
it had unfortunate results.

508
00:52:35,158 --> 00:52:37,285
[SCREAMING]

509
00:52:46,236 --> 00:52:47,931
He returned to this world...

510
00:52:48,104 --> 00:52:51,631
...but returned damaged.

511
00:53:23,240 --> 00:53:25,140
My army searched for months...

512
00:53:25,308 --> 00:53:28,709
...but we were never able to find a body
or pick up a trail.

513
00:53:29,379 --> 00:53:31,279
I thought him dead yet again.

514
00:53:31,881 --> 00:53:36,375
But I hear you have been having trouble
at home.

515
00:53:36,553 --> 00:53:40,683
I have returned your son to you
as a blight upon your house.

516
00:53:40,890 --> 00:53:42,619
He burns the very kingdom you--

517
00:53:44,127 --> 00:53:45,617
--protect.

518
00:53:51,268 --> 00:53:53,133
Shall I alert the guards to pursue him?

519
00:53:53,303 --> 00:53:56,500
Don't be foolish.
They would never catch him.

520
00:53:56,673 --> 00:53:59,699
Besides, I have done enough.

521
00:54:08,518 --> 00:54:11,851
ALFRED:
Sir, please take this to heart.

522
00:54:12,022 --> 00:54:14,422
who Jason was before,
how we lost him...

523
00:54:14,591 --> 00:54:18,186
...and this dark miracle or curse
that has brought about his return...

524
00:54:18,361 --> 00:54:20,090
...it is not your fault.

525
00:54:20,263 --> 00:54:22,925
l know you view his death
as your greatest failure but--

526
00:54:23,099 --> 00:54:25,533
His life and his death
are my greatest failure.

527
00:54:25,702 --> 00:54:27,863
Do you remember how he was
when I found him?

528
00:54:28,038 --> 00:54:33,135
of course, sir.
Fearless, arrogant, brash and gifted.

529
00:54:33,310 --> 00:54:36,677
BATMAN: Yes.
Different than Dick in so many ways...

530
00:54:36,846 --> 00:54:40,612
...but still so full of potential and power.

531
00:54:40,784 --> 00:54:44,015
But I knew, even from the beginning,
he was dangerous.

532
00:54:44,187 --> 00:54:48,385
If I hadn't made him into Robin,
he would have grown to do wrong.

533
00:54:49,059 --> 00:54:50,549
Then I got him killed.

534
00:54:50,727 --> 00:54:51,989
My partner.

535
00:54:52,162 --> 00:54:53,493
My soldier.

536
00:54:53,663 --> 00:54:54,857
My fault.

537
00:54:55,031 --> 00:54:56,396
I own that.

538
00:54:56,566 --> 00:54:59,364
I'll carry that like everything else:

539
00:54:59,536 --> 00:55:00,969
But now there's this.

540
00:55:01,137 --> 00:55:04,197
He's taken everything I've ever taught him
and turned it on me.

541
00:55:04,374 --> 00:55:06,501
it's a hell of my own making, Alfred.

542
00:55:06,676 --> 00:55:09,770
Sir, this is not your doing.
You loved him: He knows that.

543
00:55:09,946 --> 00:55:12,312
- it should be enough.
- it's not.

544
00:55:13,216 --> 00:55:14,911
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

545
00:55:15,118 --> 00:55:17,279
WOMAN ON TV:
Reporting live from Gotham Bay Bridge....

546
00:55:17,454 --> 00:55:20,355
My word.
Sir, patch into the media feed now.

547
00:55:24,094 --> 00:55:25,994
[SIRENS WAILING]

548
00:55:29,165 --> 00:55:31,326
[JOKER CACKLING]

549
00:55:31,501 --> 00:55:33,833
MAN:
Come on, get out of there, now.

550
00:55:34,637 --> 00:55:39,165
Don't know what that maniac's up to, but
nobody make a move till I give the order.

551
00:55:56,793 --> 00:55:58,761
JOKER [SINGING]:
I'm a little teapot

552
00:55:58,928 --> 00:56:00,725
Short and stout

553
00:56:01,498 --> 00:56:06,094
Here is my handle
Here is my spout

554
00:56:08,838 --> 00:56:12,535
This wasn't part of the damn deal,
you freak!

555
00:56:12,709 --> 00:56:15,542
Get me out of here right now!

556
00:56:15,712 --> 00:56:19,045
I thought you'd enjoy
seeing some old faces.

557
00:56:19,215 --> 00:56:23,311
After all, most of these guys
used to work for you.

558
00:56:24,087 --> 00:56:26,578
MAN:
who's that? Get a light on him.

559
00:56:30,093 --> 00:56:31,856
Up there.

560
00:56:37,133 --> 00:56:42,002
Hey, look at you. Mr. Hood.

561
00:56:42,172 --> 00:56:44,299
or do you prefer Red?

562
00:56:44,474 --> 00:56:46,738
I used to wear an outfit a lot like that.

563
00:56:46,910 --> 00:56:50,402
Mine was more flashy maitre d'
than motorcycle fetish.

564
00:56:50,580 --> 00:56:53,515
You kids today.

565
00:56:54,150 --> 00:56:56,141
I'm sorry, could you hold on?

566
00:56:56,319 --> 00:57:00,085
I was just in the middle of setting fire
to your gang.

567
00:57:00,256 --> 00:57:03,453
RED HOOD: Go ahead.
You think I care if that scum dies?

568
00:57:03,626 --> 00:57:06,686
Don't know. I just wanted your attention.

569
00:57:06,863 --> 00:57:09,093
RED HOOD:
You've always had my attention.

570
00:57:09,265 --> 00:57:12,701
But what I really wanted
was an audience with you.

571
00:57:13,870 --> 00:57:19,866
I'm sorry, that seems to imply
that you organized this little clambake.

572
00:57:20,043 --> 00:57:22,477
RED HOOD:
I did. Sure, I had lots of plans...

573
00:57:22,645 --> 00:57:26,843
...but the endgame was getting Black Mask
so desperate that he'd cut a deal.

574
00:57:27,016 --> 00:57:30,452
He was the only one with the connections
to get into Arkham...

575
00:57:30,620 --> 00:57:32,781
...and get you out.

576
00:57:32,956 --> 00:57:35,891
You can't trust anybody.

577
00:57:36,059 --> 00:57:39,460
So I've been bamboozled.

578
00:57:39,629 --> 00:57:41,324
oh, my.

579
00:57:41,498 --> 00:57:43,090
RED HOOD:
I wouldn't undersell it.

580
00:57:43,266 --> 00:57:45,530
it took a lot of work
to bring about our reunion.

581
00:57:45,702 --> 00:57:49,331
Reunion? Have we met before?

582
00:57:50,073 --> 00:57:52,337
RED HOOD:
Yes, we have.

583
00:57:52,509 --> 00:57:55,740
well, here's to warm memories.

584
00:58:01,818 --> 00:58:03,683
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

585
00:58:31,948 --> 00:58:33,939
[YELLS]

586
00:58:40,557 --> 00:58:42,650
[SCREAMING]

587
00:59:00,877 --> 00:59:02,276
RED HOOD OVER RADIO:
I've got him.

588
00:59:02,445 --> 00:59:06,040
You want him? Meet me at crime alley.

589
00:59:10,687 --> 00:59:12,484
[COUGHING]

590
00:59:12,655 --> 00:59:14,486
[LAUGHING]

591
00:59:15,558 --> 00:59:17,150
okay.

592
00:59:17,327 --> 00:59:19,591
So, what's the plan?

593
00:59:19,762 --> 00:59:22,094
Slumber party? Charades?

594
00:59:22,265 --> 00:59:23,789
A little Truth or Dare?

595
00:59:23,967 --> 00:59:26,492
Yes, I'll start with "dare."

596
00:59:30,740 --> 00:59:32,674
well, maybe I'll just go with "truth."

597
00:59:37,647 --> 00:59:39,478
[JOKER GRUNTING]

598
00:59:42,118 --> 00:59:44,951
RED HOOD:
Tell me, how does that feel?

599
00:59:46,055 --> 00:59:50,924
You know, it only hurts when I laugh.

600
00:59:54,297 --> 00:59:57,198
But, hey, I gotta know.

601
00:59:57,367 --> 00:59:58,595
who are you?

602
00:59:58,768 --> 01:00:03,034
You said we knew one another,
and you do seem really familiar.

603
01:00:03,206 --> 01:00:06,471
we double at the prom?
or maybe blow up a school bus together?

604
01:00:07,076 --> 01:00:09,874
RED HOOD:
No: I'm just something you helped make.

605
01:00:10,046 --> 01:00:12,708
That's pretty cryptic...

606
01:00:12,882 --> 01:00:14,179
...but interesting.

607
01:00:14,350 --> 01:00:15,612
Tell me more.

608
01:00:16,185 --> 01:00:19,677
RED HOOD:
Sure. Listen up.

609
01:00:19,856 --> 01:00:21,983
[JOKER GRUNTING]

610
01:00:41,344 --> 01:00:43,744
BATMAN:
Unreal.

611
01:00:55,024 --> 01:00:56,685
RED HOOD:
Hello.

612
01:00:58,661 --> 01:01:00,561
So glad you could make it.

613
01:01:01,097 --> 01:01:03,827
This ends tonight. All of it.

614
01:01:04,400 --> 01:01:06,960
RED HOOD:
Nobody knows that better than me.

615
01:01:18,781 --> 01:01:22,148
RED HOOD:
Ha. oh, you and your gadgets.

616
01:01:23,252 --> 01:01:25,186
You're not the only one with toys.

617
01:01:25,354 --> 01:01:26,753
[BEEPING]

618
01:01:26,923 --> 01:01:28,356
Crap.

619
01:01:42,805 --> 01:01:45,433
[GRUNTING]

620
01:02:19,742 --> 01:02:21,073
[RED HOOD LAUGHING]

621
01:02:21,244 --> 01:02:22,734
Look at you.

622
01:02:26,449 --> 01:02:27,939
I guess we should keep it even.

623
01:02:33,556 --> 01:02:35,148
Jason.

624
01:02:37,660 --> 01:02:39,287
Yes.

625
01:02:39,495 --> 01:02:41,019
BATMAN:
I don't wanna fight you.

626
01:02:41,197 --> 01:02:42,960
RED HOOD:
All evidence to the contrary.

627
01:02:43,132 --> 01:02:46,260
Please, I can help you.
I know what happened.

628
01:02:46,469 --> 01:02:48,596
oh, you got to talking with Ra's, huh?

629
01:02:48,771 --> 01:02:52,639
Does it make it easier for you to think
that my dip in his fountain of youth...

630
01:02:52,809 --> 01:02:54,606
...turned me rabid?

631
01:02:54,777 --> 01:02:56,642
or is this just the real me?

632
01:03:14,664 --> 01:03:15,722
Tell me...

633
01:03:15,898 --> 01:03:19,664
...what bothers you more, that your greatest
failure has returned from the grave?

634
01:03:19,836 --> 01:03:22,202
or that I've become a better Batman
than you?

635
01:03:23,840 --> 01:03:27,105
You're ruling through intimidation
and murder. Just another criminal.

636
01:03:27,276 --> 01:03:28,834
I'm what this city needs.

637
01:03:51,834 --> 01:03:55,861
Hidden goodies all over, huh? we're both
just a couple of walking armories.

638
01:03:56,038 --> 01:04:00,031
Maybe so,
but let's see how you do without your toys.

639
01:04:28,337 --> 01:04:29,736
Enough. it's over.

640
01:04:50,726 --> 01:04:53,752
You say you wanna be better than me.
But it won't happen.

641
01:04:53,930 --> 01:04:54,988
Not like this.

642
01:05:01,804 --> 01:05:03,635
I know I failed you...

643
01:05:03,806 --> 01:05:06,206
...but I tried to save you, Jason.

644
01:05:06,375 --> 01:05:09,674
I'm trying to save you now.

645
01:05:12,214 --> 01:05:14,341
is that what you think this is about?

646
01:05:14,517 --> 01:05:18,510
That you let me die? I don't know
what clouds your judgment worse.

647
01:05:18,688 --> 01:05:21,851
Your guilt
or your antiquated sense of morality.

648
01:05:23,326 --> 01:05:26,853
Bruce, I forgive you for not saving me.

649
01:05:27,029 --> 01:05:30,465
But why? why on God's earth...

650
01:05:31,267 --> 01:05:33,565
...is he still alive?

651
01:05:35,071 --> 01:05:37,005
[CACKLING]

652
01:05:38,808 --> 01:05:41,299
Gotta give the boy points.

653
01:05:41,477 --> 01:05:45,470
He came all the way back from the dead
to make this shindig happen.

654
01:05:45,648 --> 01:05:48,116
So who's got a camera?

655
01:05:48,284 --> 01:05:51,378
ooh! ooh!
Get one of me and the kid first.

656
01:05:51,554 --> 01:05:54,022
Then you and me, then the three of us.

657
01:05:54,190 --> 01:05:56,317
And then one with the crowbar. Then--

658
01:05:56,492 --> 01:05:58,187
[YELLS]

659
01:05:59,328 --> 01:06:02,695
You'll be as quiet as possible
or I'll put one in your lap first.

660
01:06:02,865 --> 01:06:06,130
Party pooper. No cake for you.

661
01:06:06,869 --> 01:06:09,099
ignoring what he's done in the past.

662
01:06:09,271 --> 01:06:13,799
Blind;y, stupid;y, disregarding
the entire graveyards he's filled...

663
01:06:13,976 --> 01:06:17,343
...the thousands who have suffered,
the friends he's crippled.

664
01:06:18,114 --> 01:06:19,547
You know, I thought--

665
01:06:19,715 --> 01:06:23,242
I thought I'd be the last person
you'd ever let him hurt.

666
01:06:23,652 --> 01:06:26,018
if it had been you
that he beat to a bloody pulp...

667
01:06:26,188 --> 01:06:29,419
...if he had taken you from this world,
I would've done nothing...

668
01:06:29,592 --> 01:06:34,894
...but search the planet for this pathetic pile
of evil death-worshiping garbage...

669
01:06:35,064 --> 01:06:36,759
...and sent him off to hell.

670
01:06:36,932 --> 01:06:40,732
You don't understand.
I don't think you've ever understood.

671
01:06:40,903 --> 01:06:42,461
what?

672
01:06:42,705 --> 01:06:45,503
what, your moral code
just won't allow for that?

673
01:06:45,674 --> 01:06:48,074
it's too hard to cross that line?

674
01:06:48,244 --> 01:06:51,236
No. God Almighty, no.

675
01:06:51,414 --> 01:06:53,382
it'd be too damned easy.

676
01:06:53,549 --> 01:06:55,744
All I've ever wanted to do is kill him.

677
01:06:55,918 --> 01:06:58,614
A day doesn't go by
I don't think about subjecting him...

678
01:06:58,788 --> 01:07:03,919
...to every horrendous torture
he's dealt out to others and then end him.

679
01:07:04,093 --> 01:07:07,460
Aw. So you do think about me.

680
01:07:08,097 --> 01:07:09,860
But if I do that...

681
01:07:10,032 --> 01:07:13,058
...if I allow myself to go down
into that place...

682
01:07:14,437 --> 01:07:15,904
...I'll never come back.

683
01:07:17,373 --> 01:07:22,470
why? I'm not talking about killing Penguin
or Scarecrow or Dent.

684
01:07:22,645 --> 01:07:25,409
I'm talking about him. Just him.

685
01:07:26,048 --> 01:07:28,039
And doing it because....

686
01:07:28,784 --> 01:07:30,809
Because he took me away from you.

687
01:07:32,488 --> 01:07:35,218
I can't. I'm sorry.

688
01:07:36,892 --> 01:07:39,986
That is so sweet.

689
01:07:40,596 --> 01:07:41,995
well, you won't have a choice.

690
01:07:55,444 --> 01:07:57,674
- I won't--
- This is what it's all been about.

691
01:07:57,847 --> 01:07:59,314
This.

692
01:07:59,482 --> 01:08:01,382
You, and me and him.

693
01:08:01,550 --> 01:08:03,245
Now is the time you decide.

694
01:08:05,154 --> 01:08:09,181
if you won't kill
this psychotic piece of filth, I will.

695
01:08:09,358 --> 01:08:12,122
if you wanna stop me,
you're gonna have to kill me.

696
01:08:12,294 --> 01:08:16,025
- You know I won't--
- I'm gonna blow his deranged brains out.

697
01:08:16,198 --> 01:08:19,361
And if you wanna stop it,
you are gonna have to shoot me.

698
01:08:19,535 --> 01:08:21,127
Right in my face.

699
01:08:21,303 --> 01:08:23,533
This is turning out even better
than I'd hoped.

700
01:08:34,383 --> 01:08:36,977
it's him or me, you have to decide.

701
01:08:38,821 --> 01:08:40,721
Decide now. Do it.

702
01:08:40,890 --> 01:08:44,223
Him or me? Decide.

703
01:09:00,910 --> 01:09:03,276
[JOKER CACKLING]

704
01:09:04,947 --> 01:09:06,505
I can't believe you got him.

705
01:09:06,682 --> 01:09:10,448
You expert, rooting-tooting, eagle-eyed,
goth-loving marksman.

706
01:09:10,619 --> 01:09:11,677
I love it.

707
01:09:11,854 --> 01:09:14,254
You managed to find a way to win.

708
01:09:14,423 --> 01:09:17,551
And everybody still loses.

709
01:09:26,001 --> 01:09:28,026
No, don't spoil it. This is better.

710
01:09:30,339 --> 01:09:33,502
I'm the only one who's gonna get
what he wants tonight.

711
01:09:33,676 --> 01:09:36,406
Yes, bing, bang, boom.

712
01:09:36,579 --> 01:09:37,910
we all go out together.

713
01:09:38,080 --> 01:09:41,015
Don't you just love a happy ending?

714
01:10:13,449 --> 01:10:16,009
[CACKLING]

715
01:10:29,365 --> 01:10:32,493
WOMAN ON TV: Sources close to the
district attorney's office have intimated...

716
01:10:32,668 --> 01:10:35,398
...the case will likely be dropped
due to lack of evidence.

717
01:10:35,571 --> 01:10:39,166
But the Black Mask is still under
investigation for his alleged complicity...

718
01:10:39,341 --> 01:10:41,969
...in Joker's escape from Arkham.

719
01:10:42,177 --> 01:10:44,873
The guards charged with aiding and abetting
the escape...

720
01:10:45,047 --> 01:10:47,914
...were found murdered
in the Gotham courthouse jail...

721
01:10:48,517 --> 01:10:51,315
...while the alleged crime lord, Black Mask,
was released...

722
01:10:51,487 --> 01:10:54,081
...on $1 million bail
for his suspected involvement...

723
01:10:54,256 --> 01:10:56,486
...and is currently awaiting a hearing.

724
01:10:56,659 --> 01:10:59,719
Meanwhile, the Joker has been returned
to Arkham Asylum.

725
01:10:59,895 --> 01:11:02,193
Officials claim extra measures
have been taken...

726
01:11:02,364 --> 01:11:04,764
...to ensure another escape
would be impossible.

727
01:11:05,501 --> 01:11:08,265
MAN: Prior to his arrest,
Black Mask was being strong-armed...

728
01:11:08,437 --> 01:11:11,372
...by the mysterious Red Hood.

729
01:11:19,715 --> 01:11:20,773
ALFRED:
Sir:

730
01:11:20,949 --> 01:11:24,510
in light of all the recent events,
would you like me to remove that?

731
01:11:26,555 --> 01:11:27,988
No.

732
01:11:30,125 --> 01:11:31,649
This doesn't change anything.

733
01:11:32,528 --> 01:11:34,996
it doesn't change anything at all.

734
01:11:46,742 --> 01:11:48,505
BATMAN:
okay, let's go.

735
01:11:48,677 --> 01:11:50,702
if you can't suit up quickly
at home base...

736
01:11:50,879 --> 01:11:53,347
...I'm concerned how you would handle it
in the field.

737
01:11:53,515 --> 01:11:54,743
ALFRED:
Perhaps he's primping.

738
01:11:54,917 --> 01:11:58,910
As I recall, Master Richard spent nearly
half an hour admiring his reflection...

739
01:11:59,088 --> 01:12:01,352
...the first time he donned his cape.

740
01:12:02,057 --> 01:12:05,458
Jason, get on out here
or I'm going on patrol without you.

741
01:12:05,627 --> 01:12:07,720
- Ha!
